Plan this: For the agQSL vendor-app matrix, debate whether vendor/application evidence should be labelled by application domain (pharma, finance, logistics, energy, etc.), by the type of use of quantum computing in the workload (optimisation sampler, physical simulator, kernel/feature generator, generative sampler, security primitive, error-correction/FT enabler, benchmark/tooling, etc.), or by both. The current matrix has 82 edges across 27 vendors and 13 app groups. Domain labels are useful for addressable-market and VC narratives; quantum-use labels are likely more useful for suppliers, portability analysis, and hardware/compiler matching. Produce a concrete recommendation for how to build both lenses in edges.json and in the matrix UI without creating a messy ontology.

