This is the final architectural direction I would lock in.

- Adopt the evidence-centric edge model.
- Keep `application_group` as the matrix navigation layer.
- Add both `domains` and `quantum_uses`, but do not make either primary.
- Separate `supporting_roles` from workload roles.
- Keep `quantum_inspired` out of `quantum_uses`; model it under `approach`.
- Add `claim_scope` so the UI distinguishes research, prototype, pilot, commercial, and platform capability claims.
- Use per-label `basis` and `confidence` as the target model, because many edges will have mixed certainty across labels.
- Keep vocabularies flat, small, and controlled.
